  "prompt": "What are examples of prefixes and suffixes?",
  "response": "Here are some examples:\n\nPrefixes:\n1. Un- (not): unhappy, unclear\n2. Re- (again): restart, rebuild\n3. Pre- (before): preview, prehistoric\n4. Dis- (not, opposite): disagree, dislike\n5. Sub- (under): submarine, subway\n6. Inter- (between): international, interact\n7. Non- (not): nonsense, nonverbal\n\nSuffixes:\n1. -able (capable of): readable, comfortable\n2. -tion/-sion (state of): action, tension\n3. -ness (state of being): happiness, kindness\n4. -ly (in a certain way): quickly, happily\n5. -er/-or (person who): teacher, actor\n6. -ful (full of): beautiful, careful\n7. -less (without): hopeless, fearless\n8. -ment (condition): government, development\n\nThese prefixes and suffixes can change the meaning or grammatical function of words when added to the root word.",
